      "description": "Presenting a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the legendary S54B32 inline-six, delivering linear power through six individual throttle bodies. This driver-focused example retains its tactile Getrag 420G 6-speed manual transmission and factory M-Variable differential lock. Critical preventative maintenance has been addressed, including a comprehensive VANOS overhaul and rear subframe reinforcement to ensure structural integrity under high lateral loads. The chassis is dialed in with Bilstein dampers and refreshed bushings, maintaining the precise 50/50 weight distribution these cars are known for. While the exterior shows minor road-going patina, the mechanical vitals are strong, offering a visceral 8,000 RPM redline experience for the discerning purist.",
